{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_39","type":"agent_message","text":"The fix is in [AllCoordinatesExecTask.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge6/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/5183-33b33c8f/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/tasks/AllCoordinatesExecTask.java:171). I made the nested coordinate-scoped Gradle invocations append `-Dorg.gradle.daemon=false` to `GRADLE_OPTS`, with a small helper to avoid duplicating the flag. That keeps the harness from accumulating reusable sub-build daemons across consecutive stages, which is what was driving the `run-consecutive-tests` timeout behavior for `org.eclipse.jdt:ecj:3.34.0`.\n\nVerified with the exact reproducer:\n```bash\nGRAALVM_HOME=/home/vjovanov/.sdkman/candidates/java/graalvm-ea GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=current-defaults JAVA_HOME=/home/vjovanov/.sdkman/candidates/java/graalvm-ea bash ./.github/workflows/scripts/run-consecutive-tests.sh org.eclipse.jdt:ecj:3.34.0 '[\"3.34.0\"]'\n```\nIt now completes successfully and prints `PASSED:3.34.0`.\n\nThere is still a pre-existing untracked directory at `tests/src/org.eclipse.jdt/ecj/3.26.0/test-results-native/`; I left it untouched."}}
